10:48.348 --> 10:50.049 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Hari Sreenivasan has that.

10:50.083 --> 10:54.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REX TILLERSON, U.S. Secretary of
State: Let
me be very clear: The policy of
strategic

10:54.220 --> 10:55.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
patience has ended.

10:55.989 --> 10:59.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: From South
Korea, Secretary
of State Rex Tillerson signaled
a tougher

10:59.325 --> 11:04.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
line on dealing with North
Korea, including
the possibility of a preemptive
military strike.

11:04.964 --> 11:11.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REX TILLERSON: Certainly, we do
not want to
-- for things to get to a
military conflict.

11:11.304 --> 11:18.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If they elevate the threat of
their weapons
program to a level that we
believe that requires

11:18.077 --> 11:19.846 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
action, that option is on the
table.

11:19.879 --> 11:23.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Tillerson
spoke in Seoul
after visiting the demilitarized
zone that

11:23.750 --> 11:28.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
