is publicly
opposing the proposed House
Republican health

19:50.423 --> 19:51.524 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
plan.

19:51.557 --> 19:54.527 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Dr. Andrew Gurman is its
president, and joins
me now.

19:54.560 --> 19:55.528 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Welcome to you.

19:55.561 --> 19:56.896 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

19:56.929 --> 19:57.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANDREW GURMAN, President,
American Medical
Association: Thank you.

19:57.563 --> 19:58.864 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Delighted to be here.

19:58.898 --> 19:59.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Can you boil down
the essence
of the opposition?

19:59.598 --> 20:00.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What is wrong with this plan?

20:00.566 --> 20:01.534 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

20:01.567 --> 20:03.235 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANDREW GURMAN: Sure.

20:03.269 --> 20:05.171 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that people who don't
have health
insurance live sicker and die
younger.

20:05.204 --> 20:10.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it is a basic principle of
ours that people
who have insurance shouldn't
lose it, and

20:10.242 --> 20:12.878 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
people don't have health
insurance should
get it.

20:12.912 --> 20:15.047 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we're afraid that, under
this bill, that
wouldn't happen.

20:15.081 --> 20:16.715 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, take parts of
it.

20:16.749 --> 20:22.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The tax credit part, emphasis of
this, why
wouldn't that work, or who would
that not

20:22.321 --> 20:23.289 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
work for?

20:23.322 --> 20:24.957 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

20:24.990 --> 20:26.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREW GURMAN: Well, we're
concerned that
the poorest and sickest among us
would be

20:26.859 --> 20:27.827 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
