42:39.357 --> 42:42.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Movies like 1915's "The Birth of
a Nation"
can teach us prejudice.

42:42.827 --> 42:49.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For example, take one of the
most ancient
and universal myths, vampires.

42:49.534 --> 42:56.340 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For hundreds of years, people
didn't understand
death or disease.

42:56.374 --> 43:00.178 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Why did people get sick in
bunches?

43:00.211 --> 43:04.048 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Why did people often die after
their friends
did?

43:04.081 --> 43:10.788 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, all over the world,
different civilizations
made up the same story: Death
comes from the

43:10.822 --> 43:12.390 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
undead.

43:12.423 --> 43:15.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Before the 1800s, the belief in
vampires stretched
from Transylvania to China.

43:16.027 --> 43:21.132 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Albanian vampires ate
intestines, while their
Indonesian brethren drank blood.

43:21.165 --> 43:26.771 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Eastern Europe, they
discriminated against
people they thought might become
vampires,

43:26.804 --> 43:28.840 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
including the disabled,
atheists, and even
seventh children.

43:28.873 --> 43:31.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, we know germs exists and
vampires do
not.

43:31.209 --> 43:38.549 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's tempting to say it was just
a stupid
story, but the truth is that
vampires were

43:38.583 --> 43:39.951 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the perfect story.

43:39.984 --> 43:44.822 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It didn't just explain the
mystery of death.

43:44.856 --> 43:50.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even more, it explained the
chaos of life
with a spectacular tale that
empowered villagers

43:50.628 --> 43:54.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by telling them that everybody
had the capacity
to fight evil with potions,
garlic, prayers,

43:55.032 --> 43:56.834 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
chastity, stakes, swords, and
fire.

43:56.868 --> 44:00.538 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have come a long way since
vampires.

44:00.571 --> 44:01.939 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Or have we?

44:01.973 --> 44:04.742 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Even today, society is bound by
the stories
that we tell each other.

44:04.775 --> 44:08.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In an office, loud women are
bossy, but loud
men are assertive.

44:09.013 --> 44:20.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An outspoken white person is
authoritative,
but an outspoken black person is
threatening.

44:20.591 --> 44:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Are men smarter than women, or
whites smarter
than other races?

44:29.734 --> 44:39.010 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is no scientific basis for
these ideas.

44:39.043 --> 44:43.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are stories that had to be
invented,
constructed, told, and believed.

44:43.781 --> 44:53.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From the time we are children,
we hear stories
about the way the world ought to
work.

44:53.824 --> 44:59.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From the time we are children,
we hear stories
about the way the world ought to
work.

